td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why</span><hr size=1> Might as well address a few things I saw up there in one response.<br><br>In terms of site-hosting, the Dojo (my old site) was done for free by Jirith, who did the mechanical work on that site (I didn't know much at the time about web stuff, just a writer man!).  Jir had a meg sDSL running to his house paid for by uncommongoods.com, the dot-com he was working for at the time.  He also was only willing to do (could do) a .org, which meant no revenue.<br><br>When we opened TPB Jir was working at Rutgers, and no longer had that access -- plus he was too busy.  So Sensei spent a few weeks learning php, mySQL and all the other fun stuff, built the first iteration of the site and then set out to find a host.  Problem is that while storage space isn't a big issue, bandwidth is -- the Dojo at it's peak was hitting 10gigs.  While a lot of sites offer unlimited bandwidth, the fine print always catches you, or they screw you some other way.  Also, hosting companies are going under left and right, and I wanted to find a reputable one.<br><br>Soooo, I settled on a host that offered decent bandwidth prices and all the features I needed (not every host offers MySQL and PHP for a reasonable rate).  But we are borderline from the stats I run, and a bulletin board is a HUGE bandwidth hog.  That, combined with the fact that while I did all of TPB myself it wasn't easy for me to do so, is why I went with a 3rd party board host.<br><br>BTW, for those of you wondering, since the site went live on July 27 we've had 583,563 hits and we average just over 20,000 a day.  <br><br>Of all of those that I've seen, ezBoard, even with their bullshit at times, is a great board setup.  It's easy to use, it does have some nice features and the price at least was decent.  In seeing what sites like the Safehouse are paying I'm not so sure about that, but we'll deal with that when we get there.<br><br>Anyway, on behalf of Enchant and myself I wanted to thank all of you again for your support, it is truly appreciated.<br><br>Thanks,<br><br>- Sensei<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#99CC66><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/umynxofxev.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mynx of Xev</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_ball.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Ninja Wanna-Be</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#660000>(8/30/01 9:11:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> I have no idea if this is true</span><hr size=1> But I received an e-mail yesterday that said that EZ-Board was selling out sucscribers' addrs to e-mail spammer companies. I know that about four or so months ago I became the target of mass marketing spammers. Anything from mortgage brokers to sex &quot;education&quot; providers. Geesh! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/ujaqrabbit.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jaqrabbit</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Training Dummy</span><br>  Posts: 74<br> <font color=#660000>(8/30/01 10:46:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.home.net/mcallahan/icons/martialarts.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I have no idea if this is true</span><hr size=1> heh...  I've had a hotmail address forever, so I wouldn't even notice if EZBoards was selling my address.  I'm convinced MicroShaft sold it a long time ago.  Any increase in Spam in my email box at this point would be like a dr